<recipe>
    <name>Chicken Kheema Pulao</name>
    <indexCharacter>C</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Pick basmati rice. Wash twice and soak in three cups of water for half an hour. Drain and keep aside. Wash chicken mince, drain and keep aside.

2. Peel, wash and slice onions. Peel, wash and grind ginger and garlic to a fine paste. Remove stems, wash and slit green chillies. Wash and chop tomatoes. Clean, wash and tear mint leaves. Clean, wash and finely chop coriander leaves. 

3. Heat oil in a pan, add cloves, cinnamon, green cardamoms, peppercorns, cumin sees, onions and green chillies. Saute until the onions begin to brown.

4. Add chicken mince and cook on high heat for four to five minutes.

5. Add ginger and garlic paste, red chilli powder, tomatoes, three cups of hot water, salt and basmati rice. Mix lightly.

6. Allow rice to come to a boil on high heat.

Cover the pan and cook on low heat for twelve to fifteen minutes.

7. Add mint leaves, coriander leaves and garam masala powder. Cover and cook for another five to seven minutes.

8. Remove from heat and serve hot.</instructions>
